'''''Al-Ṣaḥīḥ min Sīrat al-Nabī al-A‘ẓam''''' ({{lang-ar|الصحيح من سيرة النبي الأعظم}}) is a collection of 35 books written by Jafar Morteza Amoli, on the details of life of the Islamic prophet [[Muhammad]].<ref name=Mehr2012>Mehr News Network, [http://www.mehrnews.com/fa/NewsDetail.aspx?NewsID=1578202 April 17th 2012]</ref> The author started his research on the [[prophetic biography]] when he was twenty years old and gradually published his findings through the years. In his books, the author investigates the impact of the [[Hadith of Umar's ban on hadith|ban on hadith]] and the role of the new converts on the [[Historicity of Muhammad|credibility]] of Islamic history. He further surveys the methods used in the writing of several other [[Prophetic biography|siras]] and describes his own style on the topic.<ref>Journal of Islamic History and Civilization, Fall 2006, [http://www.noormags.com/view/fa/articlepage/862704 pp. 5-24] (free membership required)</ref> The book won the book of the year prize in Iran in 1993.<ref name=Mehr2012/>

