{{Infobox Politician |name = Anatol Petrencu |image = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1954|05|22}} |birth_place = [[Căuşeni]] |death_date = |death_place = |party = [[European Action Movement]] |otherparty = |spouse = |children = 2 |alma_mater = [[Moldova State University]] |profession = [[Historian]] |religion = [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Eastern Orthodoxy]] }}
'''Anatol Petrencu''' (born May 22, 1954, [[Căuşeni]]) is a politician and historian from the [[Republic of Moldova]]. He is a former president of the [[Association of Historians of Moldova]].
== Biography ==
Anatol Petrencu was born on May 22, 1954 in [[Căuşeni]]. He carried out his [[compulsory military service]] in the [[Soviet army]] (1972–1974). He graduated from [[Moldova State University]] in 1980 and between 1982 and 1985 he studied at [[Moscow State Institute of International Relations]]. He has been working for [[Moldova State University]] since 1985. Between 1998 and 2006 Petrencu was the president of [[Association of Historians of Moldova]]. Anatol Petrencu is a member of the [[Commission for the Study of the Communist Dictatorship in Moldova]].<ref>165/14.01.2010 Decret privind constituirea Comisiei pentru studierea si aprecierea regimului comunist totalitar din Republica Moldova, Monitorul Oficial 5-7/3, 19.01.2010</ref>
After 2007, he was the president of [[European Action Movement]] ({{lang-ro|Mişcarea Acţiunea Europeană}}).
