'''Germán Carrera Damas''' ([[Cumaná]], [[Sucre (state)|Sucre]], 28 May 1930), is a [[Venezuela]]n historian, professor and retired ambassador, author of important works of Venezuela's [[historiography]] such as ''El Culto a Bolívar'' (1969) and ''Una nación llamada Venezuela'' (1980), among other works and essays.

