[[Image:Aquincumi muzeum - lapidarium.jpg|right|thumb|210px|Aquincum-Budapest-Hungary. Museum - Lapidarium]] A '''lapidarium''' is a place where stone (Latin: ''lapis'') monuments and fragments of [[archaeology|archaeological]] interest are exhibited.
They can include stone [[epigraphy|epigraph]]s; [[statue]]s; architectural elements such as [[column]]s, [[cornice]]s, and [[acroterion]]s; [[bas relief]]s, [[tombstone]]s; and [[sarcophagus|sarcophagi]].
Such collections are often displayed in the outdoor [[courtyard]]s of [[archaeology museum]]s and [[history museum]]s. <!-- Lapidarium, a part of the [[National Museum (Prague)|National Museum]] in [[Prague]], [[Czech Republic]]. In 1995, the Lapidarium was named one of the ten most beautiful museum exhibitions in [[Europe]].<ref>[http://www.prague.net/the-lapidarium The Lapidarium - Even stone has its language | Prague.net]</ref> -->
