'''Michel Collon''' is a Belgian writer, and journalist. {{TOC right}}
==Biography== Michel Collon started his career in the Belgian weekly ''Solidaire''. He continued his work independently by writing books, making films and an Internet ''newsletter'' broadcast to 40 000 subscribers. He is affiliated with the [[Workers Party of Belgium]], and has organised a network of civil observers in [[Yugoslavia]] and in [[Iraq]]. He took part in the anti-imperialist conference Axis for Peace.<ref>[https://archive.is/20130703043958/http://www.axisforpeace.net/rubrique3.html Le colloque pour la paix dans le monde, les 17 et 18 novembre 2005], sur le site ''www.axisforpeace.net'' (page « Les participants ».</ref>
Michel Collon denounced the misuse by Dalai Lama of a photograph that implied Chinese soldiers had dressed up as [[Bhikkhu|Buddhist monks]] and had provoked the [[2008 Tibetan unrest]].<ref>Published in ''[[Le Quotidien du peuple]]'' on 3 April 2008 : [http://french.peopledaily.com.cn/vdl/vdl/6386235.html « Enquête sur une photo manipulée »]</ref> According to the [[Los Angeles Times]], this photograph was taken from the [[Michelle Yeoh]] film ''[[The Touch (2002 film)|The Touch]]'', which was filmed in Lhassa between 2001 & 2002.<ref>[http://www.latimes.com/news/nationworld/world/la-fg-monks30apr30,0,1096049.story Photo of Chinese forces with monks' robes proves illusory]</ref>
